Description: Body sherd of Attic black-figured pottery skyphos; interior glazed black; exterior: black-figure decoration consisting of head of bird, with four added red dots on neck, to left.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 362, no. B475)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0327) (Phase 1)
